
                                            Gauteng premier David Makhura has called on citizens to take back the country from politicians who are not serving them.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng premier David Makhura has called on citizens to take back the country from politicians who are not serving them. Makhura delivered the keynote address at the provinces Ethics and Anti-Corruption Indaba on Tuesday. He says he has appointed the Gauteng Ethics and Anti-Corruption Advisory Council. “We as the government can always try but never entrust everything in our hands, this is your country. If we mess up as politicians take back this country. It is yours… that includes kicking us out.” WATCH: Gauteng Ethics & Anti Corruption Indaba pt1   WATCH: Gauteng Ethics & Anti Corruption Indaba pt2  (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)